** About us: **

For more than 20 years 3Logix has been designing, developing, and deploying
high quality solutions to thousands of customers throughout Australia and New
Zealand. Over the decades we have specialised in providing a market leading
Software as a Service and In-Vehicle solutions to the ever-evolving
Environmental Services sector.

** About our Team: **

Due to the recent expansion of our client base here in Australia and New
Zealand we are seeking 2 new team member to join our existing client support
team. Based in our Murarrie, Brisbane office this front-line hands-on role
will report directly to the Support Group Team Lead.

We value an ability to learn quickly, creativity, attention to detail as well
as the ability to self-manage. Being a small team, you will have the
opportunity to communicate directly with our customers in gathering feedback
and requirements so good communication skills are essential.

** Responsibilities **

  * Provide first line of support via ticketing system, telephone, or internal referral to our clients and become their main support interface with the business. 
  * Perform remote diagnostic testing and analysis to help resolve client enquiries and request with deployed 3Logix SaaS and InCab solutions. 
  * Assist with the build and configuration of client InCab mobile PC and camera solutions. 
  * Perform QA or User Acceptance Testing of newly built client InCab or Saas solutions enhancements. 
  * The option to carry out Warranty inspections and simple InCab PC hardware repairs. 
  * Provide internal solution support to the sales and development teams 

** Essential skills required. **

  * Sound computer skills both software and hardware. 
  * Excellent communication skills (written & verbal). 
  * Good documentation skills. 

** Personal qualities & behavioral traits **

  * Flexible approach to work, be able to grow with the company as it too grows. 
  * Able to work autonomously and part of a small team. 
  * Ability to build and maintain client, supplier, and internal team member relationships. 
  * Have proven problem analysis and problem-solving skills. 
  * Organised with a sense of urgency. 
  * High attention to detail. 
  * Pride in your work. 
  * And a can-do attitude. 

